<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="Tutorial_EP17_World" s="422440">
  <T n="category">422438<!--Tutorial_EP17_Category_Life&Death--></T>
  <T n="name">0x4EF5D844<!--Welcome to Ravenwood--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_World_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:126b676281ae3bbf</T>
      <T n="text">0x8070CCFC<!--Welcome to Ravenwood, a spooky and mysterious World that bridges the gap between the living and the unliving. Here Sims can participate in any of the six festivals across the three neighborhoods, explore Crypts and haunted buildings, embark on ghostly quests, collect rare ingredients, find Lady Ravendancer Goth's legendary Tarot deck, meet collector Sims, and more...--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_World_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:126b676281ae3bbc</T>
      <T n="text">0x19D4C861<!--In the heart of Ravenwood, Crow's Crossing is a small village founded by Moppy the Goat and rumored to be frequented by Ghosts and regular hauntings. Visit the Mysterious Merchant in the old Specter graveyard for a variety of oddities, investigate the Tarot Tome Shrine on the edge of town, explore an abandoned house, or seek out the Well of Longing and Regret for a chance to make wishes come true. Just watch out for Edith!\n\nCrow's Crossing hosts a variety of Festivals:\n• Try Before You Die Casket Sale\n• Crow's Crossing Celebration of Life\n• Ravenwood Family Day\n\nBe sure to check out the <b>Town Hall</b> for more information.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_World_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:126b676281ae3bbd</T>
      <T n="text">0x1DD2E6CC<!--Nestled in the rolling hills of Ravenwood's countryside, Whispering Glen offers a quiet, rural locale for those hoping to take a step away from all the local hauntings and into a slow-paced lifestyle. Steeped in ruins and rumors, it's paradise for collectors and historians alike. Explore the local Crypt, investigate the Tarot Tome Shrine at the base of the ruins, garden in the shared community plots, or just round out a Collection.\n\nWhispering Glen also hosts a nightly festival beside the Ancestor face cliff:\n• The Moon Revelry (Clothing <i>Optional</i> during the Full Moon)--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_World_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:126b676281ae3bba</T>
      <T n="text">0x745EB00E<!--There's something otherworldly about Mourningvale. Maybe it’s the way the wind howls through the moss-draped trees, the eerie clang from the Bell Tower at odd hours, or the sentient plants. No matter the reason, many Ghosts choose to call this place home. The Grim Reaper has even been known to wander through now and then! Sims can find the Baleful Bog here, investigate the Tarot Tome Shrine by the Bell Tower, or listen to the whispers of the Guardian Tree and Alice.\n\nMourningvale hosts a variety of Festivals:\n• Afterlife Anonymous\n• Thinned Festiveil\n\nBe sure to check out the <b>Town Hall</b> for more information.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_World_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:126b676281ae3bbb</T>
      <T n="text">0x6B9292A<!--Each neighborhood in Ravenwood hosts its very own Tarot Tome Shrine. These shrines explain the mysterious origins of the Order of Lenore and their quest to reunite the missing cards from Lady Ravendancer Goth's legendary Tarot Deck. Interact with these shrines to begin your Sim's journey. Learn more in the Tarot Lesson in this section.\n\nTarot Tome Shrines can be found at the following locations:\n• Crow's Crossing: On the outskirts of town amongst the forest's edge.\n• Whispering Glen: In the bowels of an abandoned ruin, shrouded in fog as the moon rises.\n• Mourningvale: Near to the Bell Tower.\n\nYou can also interact with the Town Hall or Collector Signs in each neighborhood to pan the camera to the shrine locations.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP17\UI\Lessons\EP17_World_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:126b676281ae3bb8</T>
      <T n="text">0x9F2B1263<!--There are Collector Signs and Sims in each of the three neighborhoods. What's a Collector? Well it's a Sim who will buy your Collection items! You can <b>Read Sign</b> to learn more about their schedule, then show up when a Collector is around to sell those extra items and earn a few Simoleons in the process.--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
